The House Committee on Governmental Affairs offers the following substitute to HB 140:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 1 of Chapter 81 of Title 36 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to local government budgets and audits, so as to cap the amount of funds derived
3 from court fines or forfeiture action that municipalities may use as part of their yearly
4 budgets; to provide that any funds collected in excess of such cap shall escheat to the state;
5 to supersede any conflicting home rule powers of municipalities; to provide for applicability;
6 to provide a short title; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
7 purposes.
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
9 SECTION 1.
10 This Act shall be known and may be cited as the "End Local Taxation by Citation Act."
11 SECTION 2.
12 Article 1 of Chapter 81 of Title 36 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
13 local government budgets and audits, is amended by revising Code Section 36-81-10, relating
14 to effect of article on right to make expenditures and raise revenue, and effect on home rule
15 powers, as follows:
